cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.DS

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper deals with wireless network communication and quality-of-service requirements.
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper discusses the tradeoff between performance and complexity of distributed algorithms.
3. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is relevant as the paper focuses on distributed algorithms for wireless networks.
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper deals with interference modeling and scheduling in wireless networks.
5. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is less likely but still relevant as the paper discusses the performance guarantees of distributed algorithms.
